<div id="tableContainer">
    <h1>Variants</h1>

    <p>
        This is a collection of different dealer's choice card games and rules. Yes, our main game is still Texas
        Hold-em. If you have a favorite game contact Richard.
    </p>

    <div>
        <h2>Stud Games</h2>

        <div>
            <h3>7 Card Stud</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>3 cards are dealt to each player, 2 down, 1 up.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>1 card is dealt to each player with betting after each until all 7 cards are dealt.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>3 cards down, 4 up.</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>5 Card Stud</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>2 cards are dealt to each player, 1 down, 1 up.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>1 card is dealt to each player with betting after each until all 5 cards are dealt.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>2 cards down, the rest up.</span></li>
                            <li><span>Force betting each round</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Blind Stud</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Seven cards are dealt, 6 down 1 up. Players may not peak at their hole cards.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Everyone turns over one card with a round of betting after each until all cards are turned over.</span>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Low Ball</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Played like 7-card stud except low hand wins. A perfect low hand being 2-3-4-5-7</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Ace can go high or low</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Hi-Low</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Same rules as 7 card stud except High hand and Low hand split half the pot.</span></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Wild Cards</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Before dealing, dealer can make any card or set of cards wild. This can apply to almost any game variation.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Natural cards win over wilds. For example a natural A high flush beats a wild card flush. This rule should be stated ahead of time.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Match low card in hole and it is wild. </span></li>
                            <li><span>Low card period is wild.</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Roll Your Own</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Played like 7 card stud, cards are dealt face down with the player having the option which card to show each time.</span>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Follow the Queen</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Deal as standard 7 card stud</span></li>
                    <li><span>The Queen is wild and any card that follows.</span></li>
                    <li><span>If Queen is last card dealt up then no other wilds</span></li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Pay for Queen</span></li>
                            <li><span>Queen not wild</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>High Chicago</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Deal as standard 7 card stud</span></li>
                    <li><span>High - Highest Spade in the hole takes half the pot</span></li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Low Chicago - Lowest Spade in the hole takes half the pot</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Day Baseball</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                    <li><span>Deal as standard 7 card stud</span></li>
                    <li><span>3's &amp; 9's are wild. 4 gets an extra card</span></li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Pay for extra card</span></li>
                            <li><span>Extra card may be up or down.</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Night Baseball</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                    <li><span>3's &amp; 9's are wild. 4 gets an extra card. </span></li>
                    <li><span>Deal 7 cards face down, no peaking.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Starting at the left of the dealer player turns over cards until they can beat the previous player or until they are out of cards. There is a round of betting after each player. </span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Play ends when all cards have been turned over or there is one clear winner. </span></li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Pay for extra card</span></li>
                            <li><span>Extra card may be up or down.</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Draft Stud</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Deal as normal stud. 2 cards down, one up.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Best hand showing bets. </span></li>
                    <li><span>The number of players cards are dealt face up in center. </span></li>
                    <li><span>Starting with the lowest hand, going to the highest hand each player picks the </span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Best hand showing bets.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Repeat until all 7 cards are dealt.</span></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <h2>Draw Games</h2>

        <div>
            <h3>Draw</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>5 cards are dealt to each player down.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Starting to the left of the dealer each player may request up to 3 additional cards to complete their hand, throwing away a matching number of cards.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Variations</span>
                        <ol type="a">
                            <li><span>Player may request 4 cards if holding an Ace or wild card.</span></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Pass the Trash</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                    <li><span>7 cards are dealt</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>1 card is past to left</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>2 card is past to left</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>3 card is past to left</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Pick-em Draw</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Two cards are dealt to players face down.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>(Number of Players + 1) sets of 3 cards are dealt in the middle, two cards face down, one card face up. Starting to the left of the dealer each player gets to pick a stack.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h3>Countdown</h3>

            <div>
                <ol>
                    <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                    <li><span>Deal 5 cards face down. </span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Each player may replace zero to three cards. For X fee.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Each player may replace zero to two cards. For 2X fee</span></li>
                    <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    <li><span>Each player may replace zero to one card. For 4X fee.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Best hand wins.</span></li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h2>Community Card Games</h2>

            <div>
                <h3>Texas Hold-em</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Two cards are dealt to each player face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Three community cards are dealt up</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>One community card is dealt up.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>One Community card is dealt up. </span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Best hand is made from a combination of two hole cards and community cards.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Variations</span>
                            <ol>
                                <li><span>Force players to bet each round to stay in.</span></li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Omaha Hold-em</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Four cards are dealt to each player face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Three community cards are dealt up</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>One community card is dealt up.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>One Community card is dealt up. </span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li>
                            <span>Best hand is made from combination of community cards and 2 out of 4 hole cards.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Variations</span>
                            <ol type="a">
                                <li><span>Force players to bet each round to stay in.</span></li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Pineapple Hold-em</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Texas Hold-em rules apply, however instead of 2 cards, 3 cards are dealt face down to player and one card is discarded.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Variations</span>
                            <ol type="a">
                                <li><span>Crazy Pineapple - Card discarded after the flop. </span></li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Pyramid Hold-em</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Similar rules to Omaha</span></li>
                        <li><span>Deal four cards face down to players. </span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Deal a row of 1 card, a row of 2 cards and a row of 3 cards face down.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Turn over the top card, player must use this card in their hand.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li>
                            <span>Turn over second row of cards, player must use 1 of the two cards in this row.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn over third row of cards, player must use 1 of the three cards in this row.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Variations</span>
                            <ol type="a">
                                <li><span>Reverse the pyramid 3, 2, 1 instead of 1, 2, 3.</span></li>
                                <li><span>Hourglass, 3, 1, 3 setup.</span></li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Frame</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Player uses 2 cards in their hand and one side of the community board.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Deal two cards to players face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li>
                            <span>Deal 8 cards face down on the board in a square pattern. Flip the center 4 cards.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Flip each corner card with betting after each.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Tic Tac Toe</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Player uses 2 cards in their hand and one row on the board. Row can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Deal two cards to players face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>A row of 3 cards are dealt face up with a round of betting after each row. Repeat until all 9 cards are shown.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Criss Cross</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                        <li><span>5 Cards are dealt as community cards in a cross pattern. Cards are in the players hands.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>2-5 cards are dealt to each player face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn over one community card with a round of betting after each.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Middle card is wild.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Variations</span>
                            <ol type="a">
                                <li>
                                    <span>If player has middle card in their had, then hand is thrown away.</span>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Wild Pitch</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Normal poker hands apply</span></li>
                        <li><span>7 Cards are dealt. The first 3 cards are turned over and are wild. The last 3 cards are turned over and if they are in your hand they have to be thrown away. </span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>7 cards are dealt to each player face down.</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn over one community card with a round of betting after each.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Oh Crap</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>3 cards are dealt to each player face down. 4 Cards are dealt as community cards. Cards are in the players hands.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn 1st community card</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn 2nd community card</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Turn 3rd community card, this card is wild</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li>
                            <span>Turn 4th community card, if this card is in your hand then you throw away your hand.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Cincinnati</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Each player is dealt four hole cards</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>4 community cards are dealt face up one at a time with betting after each turn.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Best hand is made with 4 cards on board and 4 in hand.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Lame Brain Pete</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Each player is dealt 3 hole cards</span></li>
                        <li><span>Four total community cards. One card is turned over with a round of betting after each.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>The lowest card on the board is wild and all like them.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h3>Otis Elevator</h3>

                <div>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span>Each player is dealt 4 hole cards. 7 community cards are dealt down in an "H" formation: two vertical lines of cards, and one card in the center between the two lines.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Two corner cards are turned over </span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Other two corner cards are turned over</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Two middle cards are turned over </span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>Middle card is turned over</span></li>
                        <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                        <li><span>The center card is the "elevator card", and can be positioned on any of the three "floors" created by the two vertical lines. Player can match their hole cards to any of the three floors to make a hand.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <h2>Progressive Games</h2>

                <div>
                    <h3>Jacks are Better Trips to Win</h3>

                    <div>
                        <ol>
                            <li><span>Deal players 5 cards, face down.</span></li>
                            <li><span>Starting to the left of the dealer, if any player has a pair of Jacks or better they can open. If not then the cards are thrown away and re-dealt with a new ante until someone can open.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Betting, player must have at least a 3 of a kind to win the whole pot. If no three of a kind is made then hands are re-dealt. If a player drops then they are out for all re-deals.</span>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Guts</h3>

                    <div>
                        <ol>
                            <li><span>Deal 2 cards face down.</span></li>
                            <li>
                                <span>Dealer says 1, 2, 3 Drop. Anyone that does not want to stay drops their cards.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span>Each player still in is then dealt 3 more cards. Best hand wins the pot. Loser matches the pot.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Play continues until only 1 player stays and beats 5 random cards dealt from the deck.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Variations</span>
                                <ol type="a">
                                    <li><span>Limit amount losing player has to pay.</span>
                                    </li>
                                    <li><span>+ 2's &amp; 3's are wild.</span></li>
                                    <li><span>Chicken Rule: If no one stays in for a hand highest two cards has to pay a fee into the pot.</span>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Spit</h3>

                    <div>
                        <ol>
                            <li><span>Deal 2 cards face down.</span></li>
                            <li><span>At any point during deal someone yells Spit and the dealer turns up a card, then that card and all like it are wild. Wild card is not in your hand.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Each player to the left of the dealer says if they are in or out. </span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Each player still in is then dealt 3 more cards, face down. Best hand wins the pot. Loser matches the pot.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Play continues rotating the dealer until only 1 player stays and beats 5 random cards dealt from the deck.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li><span>Variations</span>
                                <ol type="a">
                                    <li>
                                        <span>Limit amount losing player has to pay</span>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    <h2>Other Games</h2>

                    <div>
                        <h3>Scoopa</h3>

                        <div>
                            <ol>
                                <li><span>Deal 4 cards</span></li>
                                <li><span>Toss 1 and bet</span></li>
                                <li><span>4 Total community cards, flip one at a time, bet after each one. If a card in your hand matches one on the board then throw that card away. If board pairs, then throw away and flip another community card</span>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Numbered cards are worth face value, face cards are 10, Aces 1 or 11. </span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>If someone throws in all the cards in their hand, then they take the whole pot.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Low number and high number split the pot.</span>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                        <h3>7 / 27</h3>

                        <div>
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Numbered cards are worth face value, face cards are &#189;, Aces 1 or 11. </span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Closest to 7 and 27 without going over split the pot.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Deal 2 cards, one down, one up</span></li>
                                <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                                <li><span>Dealer asks player if they want a card and gives it to them. </span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Betting</span></li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Player can only pass 3 times and take any number of cards without busting.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Betting ends when no one takes a card.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Variations</span>
                                    <ol type="a">
                                        <li><span>Player can pass any number of times</span>
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span>7 &#189; &amp; 21 &#189;</span></li>
                                        <li><span>Can go over.</span></li>
                                    </ol>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                        <h3>In Between</h3>

                        <div>
                            <ol>
                                <li><span>Dealer places two cards in front of them. </span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Dealer asks each player if the next card dealt will be in between the previous two cards. Player may pass or state how much they want to bet that it will be within the two cards. If card comes in between the two cards then the player wins that amount. If the card falls outside those two cards then player pays that amount to the pot. If the card is the same as an end card then the player pays double that amount.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Play continues until all of the pot is gone.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Variations.</span>
                                    <ol type="a">
                                        <li>
                                            <span>Limit amount you can lose.</span>
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span>Limit amount you can bet for the first time around the table. ex. half the pot.</span>
                                        </li>
                                    </ol>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Screw Your Neighbor</h3>

                        <div>
                            <ol>
                                <li><span>Player places 3 chips in front of them.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Each player is dealt 1 card face down.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Starting to the left of the dealer that person has the option to trade with the person to their left. Dealer may trade with the deck.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li><span>Aces are lowest card, Kings are highest and must be flipped up immediately. A King can not be traded.</span>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Player with lowest card in hand has to place one chip in the pot. </span>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <span>Rounds continue passing the deal until only one person is left with chips.</span>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>

